# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# F6 — parent-child stem duplication. 94 hits. The systematic-naming
# pair `bench/bench_*` and `scripts/deploy/deploy_*` represents an
# established intra-namespace convention (every bench file is "the
# bench tool for X", every deploy file is "the deploy script for vN").
# Renaming would force renaming ~94 files across ~15 evidence chains.
#
# Glob policy: explicit narrow patterns at the systematic-naming
# boundary. `bench/bench_*.hexa` is the entire jurisdiction-out class.
# `scripts/deploy/deploy*.hexa` is the entire jurisdiction-out class.
# Singletons (`bench/bench.hexa`, `tests/tests.hexa`,
# `scripts/deploy/deploy.hexa`) listed explicitly.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# bench/* — 73 entries via narrow glob covering bench_*.hexa convention.
bench/bench.hexa                                   | * | bench namespace entry-point [jurisdiction-out: bench] — owner: anima | 2027-04-26
bench/bench_*.hexa                                 | * | bench namespace systematic naming convention — bench_<topic>.hexa is the contract [jurisdiction-out: bench] — owner: anima | 2027-04-26

# scripts/deploy/* — deploy snapshots, version-pinned to specific GPU host configs.
scripts/deploy/deploy.hexa          | * | deploy entry-point [jurisdiction-out: deploy] — owner: anima | 2027-04-26
scripts/deploy/deploy_v*_h100.hexa  | * | deploy namespace systematic naming — deploy_v<N>_h100.hexa snapshots [jurisdiction-out: deploy] — owner: anima | 2027-04-26

# tests/tests.hexa — top-level test entry-point convention.
tests/tests.hexa | * | tests namespace entry-point [jurisdiction-out: bench] — owner: anima | 2027-04-26
